  "body": "Lesson learned from #6156 \r\n\r\nA node should prevent users change `--slots-per-archive-point` in flight. Meaning if a user has set `slots-per-archive-point` to 256 to being with. The node should prevent the user changing it to 2048 or any value once the node begin to operate. \r\n\r\nThe consequence of changing `--slots-per-archive-point` in flight will create inconsistency of archived points mapping. That results in poor UX for the users.",
